import React from 'react'
import useInputState from './hooks/useInputState'
import { Paper, ListItem, TextField, Grid, Button } from '@material-ui/core'

function LoginForm() {
    const [value, handleChange] = useInputState("")
    return (
        <Grid container justify="flex-end" alignItems="center" direction="column">
            <Paper style={{ width: "20%", padding: "2rem" }}>
                <form>
                    <TextField onChange={handleChange} id="outlined-basic" label="Username" variant="outlined" value={value} fullWidth />
                    <TextField onChange={handleChange} id="outlined-password-input"
                        label="Password"
                        type="password"
                        autoComplete="current-password"
                        variant="outlined"
                        value={value}
                        fullWidth
                    />
                    <Button variant="contained" color="primary" style={{ marginTop: "1rem" }} >Login</Button>
                </form>
            </Paper>
        </Grid>
    )
}

export default LoginForm
